<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> pull foot • pull someone’s leg</xh5><p> <i>pull foot</i>—(dated) leave in a hurry; run with all one’s might: The whole crew <u>pulled foot</u> as if Old Nick had held them in chase.</p><p><i>pull someone’s leg</i>—(coll.) tease or mislead smb. humorously: Stanley knew they were <u>pulling his leg</u>, but instead of finding it amusing he felt uneasy.</p><p> <i>See also: drag one’s feet</i> / <i>drag one’s foot.</i></p> </entry>
